..TEXT:
|gliel'~ = ^gliele.~ ^Le~ is invariable and can represent ^lo,
li~, or ^la~; in this case it is ^la~, a form common to many idioms in
Italian.  Thus, ^accoccarla ad uno~ means "to let someone have it," "to
deal someone an ugly blow."
